INSERT INTO public.responses (question_id, question_text, llm_response, original_answer, bert_score, processing_attempts, total_processing_time_ms, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('78f0ade76d6037b0', '1. The age old moral and ethical values are disappearing among children. Is it due to our education system?', 'No es la ├║nica causa. Aunque el sistema educativo puede influir, la erosi├│n de valores suele ser resultado de m├║ltiples factores: la familia, la sociedad y los medios de comunicaci├│n tambi├⌐n juegan un papel fundamental.', 'I think that the education system does contribute to the lowering of values and standards, but only because the education system mirrors the greater society. If you know people who work in schools, often parents themselves interfere with a school''''s attempt to discipline their children--to keep standards and values strong.\n\nParents do have a lot to do with their children''''s values and standards. I think that a lot of parents have wanted their children to be happy at all costs, and many have chosen to let their kids do whatever they want, not work hard for what they get, and do lots of activities that children didn''''t used to get to do. So, watching cable TV, using the Internet, listening to adult-themed music all has a negative effect on children''''s values. And when they get to school and hang around with peers who have weak values it reinforces poor values.\n\nFinally, I think that the breakdown of the usual society structures that previously enforced a higher sense of values and purposes--church, neighborhood, nuclear and extended families, for example--have also weakened our values and standards.', 0.638456404209137, 1, 500, '2025-09-16 07:13:25.827391', '2025-09-16 07:13:25.827391');
