INSERT INTO public.responses (question_id, question_text, llm_response, original_answer, bert_score, processing_attempts, total_processing_time_ms, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('97345838ace819bc', 'Should Joe Crede have won the White Sox MVP for the 2005 World Series?', 'No. Jermaine Dye fue el MVP oficial de la Serie Mundial 2005. Aunque Joe Crede tuvo una excelente serie (particularmente a la defensiva y con un jonr├│n crucial), Dye tuvo un promedio de bateo superior (.438) y el hit decisivo en el ├║ltimo partido.', 'Mmm... it''''s close.\n\nDye: 7/16, .438, 3 R, 2B, HR, 3 RBI, 2 BB, 2 K\nCrede: 6/17, .353, 2 R, 2B, 2 HR, 3 RBI, 1 BB, 2K\n\nYou''''ll see that Dye edges out Crede in BA, R, and BB, while Crede''''s only claim to fame is an extra HR, though both had the same number of RBI.\n\nDye homered with 2 outs in Game 1, and RBI with 2 outs are always important.  He left none on base in Game 1, while Crede left one on.  Game 2, neither left any one on base.  Game 3, Dye left three on base, Crede left one, and Dye also grounded into a double play.  Game 4, Dye left none on base, Crede left one, but Dye had another 2-out RBI, and the only RBI of that game.\n\nI think that Dye''''s stats are slightly in his favor, the gameplay stats are about even, and Dye''''s game-winning RBI with two outs pushes him over the edge as the most deserving MVP candidate.', 0.621394157409668, 1, 500, '2025-09-16 21:14:58.100418', '2025-09-16 21:14:58.100418');
