INSERT INTO public.responses (question_id, question_text, llm_response, original_answer, bert_score, processing_attempts, total_processing_time_ms, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('fb479ec1bf21006f', 'what do you tip a nyc apartment building doorman?', 'En la temporada navide├▒a. Un rango com├║n es de **$50 a $150 por doorman**, dependiendo del tiempo que llevas viviendo all├¡ y del nivel de servicio.', 'we had that same issue last year. I would say 20-80.\nit really depends on your relationship with him:\n1. is he the only doorman or it is a group of a few? (Cannot give them $50 each, right?)\n2. is he friendly? can you trust him to let someone in - a friend, a Plummer,  delivery of any kind etcΓÇÖ\n3. is he also the super of the building? If yes then is he good?\n\nIn general, if someoneΓÇÖs impact on your life is significant, then I think that a yearly $80 tip is a good investment.\n\nSince you are talking on a group of 6, I would suggest that you tip the manager of the group 50 and the rest $30. I would guess that this is a building with many apartments, thus the reason for so many doormen. They donΓÇÖt expect you to tip them $50 each, they know it is impossible.\n\nAnother thing that you can do is to bring a nice pail of candy to make them happy (and forget that you were cheap on the tip)', 0.5831872224807739, 1, 500, '2025-09-16 18:31:54.324788', '2025-09-16 18:31:54.324788');
