INSERT INTO public.responses (question_id, question_text, llm_response, original_answer, bert_score, processing_attempts, total_processing_time_ms, created_at, updated_at) VALUES ('119510d2e7721e46', 'If people are to blame nature or society for being evil, why do they go to hell for what they are? ..jff, JFF?', 'Se reconoce que la naturaleza o la sociedad pueden **influir** en la maldad. Sin embargo, la condena al infierno (en un contexto religioso) se basa en la creencia en el **libre albedr├¡o**. Se considera que la persona, a pesar de las influencias, es responsable de sus propias **decisiones y acciones**, y por lo tanto es juzgada por lo que *hace*, no solo por lo que *es* o por lo que le afecta.', '1.  I believe that God will take into account the forces that shape us when we face him for the final reckoning.\n\n2.  "Blame", or rather responsibility, is not divided when it is shared.  I may be fully responsible for my actions, but if I act the way my father taught me to act, he too has some responsibility for my behavior.  \n\n3. In reality, people who do evil almost never think they are doing anything wrong.  Hitler thought he was cleaning the world of inferior humans when he sent homosexuals, gypsies and jews to concentration camps.  When you see a criminal blame society for their crimes, it''''s usually more in the way of lashing back out at the people who are putting them into jail than trying to explain their actions.\n\n4.  For those of us try to explain how certain circumstances led to a person''''s actions, we are not trying to excuse their behaviour, we are trying to *understand* it so that we can prevent it EFFECTIVELY.  How can you fix a problem if you don''''t understand what caused it? Before you say "That''''s what prisons are for", I will point you to recidivism rates. When someone is sent to jail, society loses almost all of the leverage that the threat of punishment provides.  So we have to understand how people get to the point that the threat of punishment doesn''''t work before we can effectively stop crime.', 0.6290070414543152, 2, 1000, '2025-09-16 12:30:23.866427', '2025-09-16 12:30:23.866427');
